<p>I have already configured the reverse proxy for the  <a href="http://msdhoni.com" rel="nofollow">http://msdhoni.com</a> to 192.168.6.190  <br/> <a href="http://msdhoni.com" rel="nofollow">http://msdhoni.com</a> has many users for its site.<br/> Now when I type <a href="https://ganguly.msdhoni.com" rel="nofollow">https://ganguly.msdhoni.com</a> (where ganguly is one of the user), it should redirect to <a href="https://msdhoni/Profiles/ganguly" rel="nofollow">https://msdhoni/Profiles/ganguly</a>.<br/> The code I used was </p>  <pre><code>server {             access_log /var/log/nginx/subcalls.log;                     proxy_set_header        Host            $host;                     proxy_set_header        X-Real-IP       $remote_addr;                     proxy_set_header        X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;              add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin *;             listen  80;             server_name ~^(?&lt;subdomain&gt;.+)\.msdhoni\.com$;               location /             {                     proxy_pass      http://192.168.6.190/Profiles/$subdomain/default.aspx$request_uri/;             }             } </code></pre>  <p>the subdomain refers to user ganguly</p>